oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Proceedings of the Fourth Annual Conference (1971). What We Expect from a Veterinarian
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Crusch, Fay
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: ranching
herd performance
Angus
veterinary practice
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Our speaker this noon is a cattleman. He was ranch-born and raised and owns an operation of 4500 acres near Bainville, Montana. He began ranching in 1940. He has an extremely well managed registered and commercial Angus operation and has been doing herd performance testing work and research since 1959. He has also had experience as a farm news reporter for a 12-station network in the Northwest for ten years and television experience for eight years. So, it gives me great pleasure to introduce to you Mr. Fay Crusch. (Applause) Address presented during the noon luncheon, Wednesday, December 15, 1972
